Name: Tin (Straits, Pigs) Prices (US Cents/Pound)
Periodicity:
Monthly From Jan 1803 To Dec 1911
Daily From Jan 1912 To Dec 1921
Monthly From Jan 1922 To Jun 1989
Daily From Jul 1989 To Jun 2018
Monthly From Jul 2018 To Aug 2020
Metadata: Prices are for Straits Tin and taken from Anne Bezanson, Wholesale prices in Philadelphia, 1784-1861 (published 1936-1937) and 1852-1896 (published 1954): a series of relative monthly prices. Philadelphia: University of Pennsylvania Press, 1936-1937 and 1954 from 1803 through 1879, and from the NBER from 1880 to 1957 who used issues of the Engineering and Mining Journal from 1880 through 1899, and for 1900 through 1957, Metal Statistics.  Data are the average of weekly quotations for 1880-1884 and the average of daily quotations from 1885 through 1958.  Data from 1958 to November 1985 is the London Metal Exchange spot quote from Metals Week, from December 1985 to June 1989, the Malyasian Straits, minimum 99.85% purity, Kuala Lumpur Tin Market settlement price, and from 1986 on the price of tin, standard grade, spot, c.i.f. in New York.
